 you so much!  I have really been enjoying the site - I appreciate the work you and your team have put into it!  You can reach me at:<br />\nBrian Platt<br />\n2302 E. 27th Terrace<br />\nLawrence, KS 66046<br />\nI wish you continued success with Collectors\' Quest!<br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-31 21:15:51'),(263,'42c909c19bcafafa587713d1538288ed',109,118,'RE: RE: hey','Hey Mike,<br />\nThis site does kick ass! I was invited also to post my Star Wars collection. I was on your website, I see a few things there that I may be interested in. I will be keeping in touch with you from time to time. I have a few more things to post also, one is a 1976/77 set of 15 Star Wars Blueprints, really cool!! Keep in touch.<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-31 21:40:34'),(264,'42c909c19bcafafa587713d1538288ed',109,118,'RE: RE: RE: RE: hey','Mike, we have something in common, I too sold what I originally had for very, very cheap and it\'s something that I can kick myself in the ass for!<br />\nA man not to far from me use to own a second hand/trading/hobby store and now everything is in his basement, he has a ton of vintage Star Wars figures, I am trying to buy them from him and he always says he\'ll sell them to only me, but he\'s older and I still haven\'t had a chance to get them!!!<br />\nI started collecting again in 1998/99 and been buying pretty much ever since. You\'ll notice that I don\'t have much EII figures, that\'s because money was short during that time, but I have tons of EI, EIII and Saga figures. My personal favs are the vintage stuff. I buy a lot of ebay.<br />\nI am going to add you to my buddies and you can do the same. How much is shipping to Canada? My postal code is A2H4M9. To give you an idea, say if I bought 5 or 6 figures to start, how much to ship them?<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-31 22:07:00'),(265,'42c909c19bcafafa587713d1538288ed',109,118,'RE: RE: hey','I buy a lot of ebay also, ebay is wonderful!! The only favor I\'d ask of you is if I did buy from your site that you\'d write gift on the package so I wouldn\'t have to pay duty. If you wouldn\'t do that I completely understand. I do buy a lot from the States also. I use to just stick with Canada, seeing I am from here, and then I found that some people were over charging on certain items and shipping so I took my business elsewhere.<br />\nI have those blueprints up now if you wanted to take a look,  STAR WARS OTHER VINTAGE is where you\'ll find them and their the last picture, so just click 2nd page. Feel free to leave comments. These blueprints are really cool, I never seen anything like them before. They are from 1977 and I have to be honest, I love the vintage stuff!!<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-31 22:56:00'),(266,'2901cfb3e839d415b93afe08883ccd0f',1,120,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-01 10:30:56'),(267,'d79367e4416505016a67bbde69d3695e',1,121,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-01 11:43:37'),(268,'42c909c19bcafafa587713d1538288ed',109,118,'RE: RE: hey','Hey Mike,<br />\nSome people are so odd, ebay has many kinds of people!! I was lucky with what I bougth, mainly because I stick with a few good sellers, but it\'s a risk!! I had a few people that tried to rip me off with stuff, like they give me shipping cost for an item and when I won it they jacked the price up to 3 times what they said it was, this is why I ask before bidding and I save the email. Any way, they never got away with it and I got the item for what they originally said shipping was and I never bought from them again.<br />\nThose blueprints are pretty cool! I got them in Canada, off ebay. I think I only paid $60.00 or $70.00 for them. I love rare items!!<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-01 11:47:12'),(269,'933a69faf131160bab18052b0e246277',109,12,'question','How did you get a Collection Profile: section? It looks very cool!! I love you collections.<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 06:19:10'),(270,'4066dd678f18af328be0af77eaabd27d',6,52,'RE: RE: Package to Send','Brian,<br />\nGreat. Hope to get it off to you shortly. Probably next week as I am slammed here.<br />\nLove all of the stuff you have put up. We\'re looking exactly for collectors like yourself. Passionate and will stop at nothing to get new finds! We\'re starting a huge marketing campaign soon so tell your friends.<br />\nAlso let us know what you like and what you don\'t like as we are looking for feedback. It\'s definitely a work in progress.<br />\nLiz',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 15:20:48'),(271,'e0795f696d381c831fb86dfd62013590',109,6,'RE: Oh Canada','Hey Liz,<br />\nThanks for writing me, I was actually going to write you soon, so this worked out pretty good. I love this site, I can\'t express enough thanks that you created something like this! I seen that I am featured and thank you very much, I love being featured!<br />\nI have been telling people about this site. I have several hardcore collector friends, so I hope that they join and showcase what they have.<br />\nSomething I would love to see is more on the profile side of the site. The profile currently is pretty limited in information....just an idea. Keep in touch with me from time to time and I will do the same with you. Thank you once again for having this idea of creating a collectors site!<br />\nYour pal<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 20:50:32'),(272,'933a69faf131160bab18052b0e246277',109,12,'RE: RE: question','Hey,<br />\nhttp://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/12/batman-a-phenalia.html (on the bottom) or in the Batman-a-phenalia section. It looks really cool!!  Hmmm, it\'s actually on all your links.<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 20:56:00'),(273,'933a69faf131160bab18052b0e246277',109,12,'RE: RE: RE: RE: question','Ok, cool and thank you very much. This is an awsome site, I am so happy that I was asked to join and upload my collection! Very cool.<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 21:23:08'),(274,'9319467fb284d23ee9bb433e24eabc10',6,5,'hawaiian tropic','hey you - get off!!! you are supposed to be relaxing. go and lay on the beach!<br />\nbtw, looks like we already have proof of concept for the dealer side - did you see flashback toy world guy. we\'ll need to put up paypal when you get back.',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-02 23:59:13'),(275,'e0795f696d381c831fb86dfd62013590',109,6,'RE: RE: RE: Oh Canada','Hey Liz,<br />\nJust a few ideas that I would like to see as a part of the profile site.<br />\nMaybe the ability to upload a short home video. Your video section is really cool and if we had a chance to upload our own home video expressing our interest in collecting that would be so cool.<br />\nThe ability to upload more then just one profile pic.<br />\nA chatroom would be cool to get the other collectors chatting.<br />\nThese are just a few ideas. Thanks :o)<br />\nCarson',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-03 04:02:09'),(276,'b3540df9e31e82e73563b7be01b47eac',109,12,'RE: Collection Profile?','Hey, thanks....Liz contacted me last night and I got it figured out now. Thanks for the help. That little extra is pretty cool and I am surprised that I did see it before Liz told me. How long have this site been up and running? Do you guys have any tie ins with FANatical? Your videos are really cool... I don\'t know if that\'s a show in the States only or if it\'s something done only for the website, but it\'s really cool. You could have a TV show based on this site and it would be a major hit.',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-03 09:26:09'),(277,'4479bdb2f8bd8d5fd5c1070000a67274',109,6,'Question','Hi Liz,<br />\nHow long have this site been up and running? Do you guys have any tie ins with FANatical? Your videos are really cool... I don\'t know if that\'s a show in the States only or if it\'s something done only for the website, but it\'s really cool. You could have a TV show based on this site and it would be a major hit.<br />\nCarson',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-03 09:27:21'),(278,'933a69faf131160bab18052b0e246277',109,6,'RE: RE: Question','Hi Liz,<br />\nYou are welcome and I am happy that I could help. Any time I can do something let me know, even if it\'s just an idea. I know that FANatical has Amercian\'s on the show aswell, so this was why I asked and it\'s also based on collecting.<br />\nCarson',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-03 12:16:09'),(279,'e0795f696d381c831fb86dfd62013590',109,6,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: Oh Canada','Yes, thanks for the help. I like the fact that I can add in a little more information. That\'s cool that you guys are going to put video on the profile. The chatroom is a bit iffy, but IMing is a cool thing if you go ahead with that idea. I would love to attend one of the events you guys put off, one day I guess. Meanwhile, keep posting the videos, I love them!!<br />\nYour friend<br />\nCarson',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-03 12:20:14'),(280,'30fcb3318030074cd9d761dce83b16c1',1,123,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectors