 I had an Ebay store until March and now I have a Record store in our town, Lansing, Michigan. I do have a lot of things that I do need to list in the next day or so. The URL for the store is flatblackandbeautifulrecords.net.<br />\nDo you have a site? I am interested in what others may have .<br />\nAnyway keep checking in the next 2 days and I will havd some cool stuff up.<br />\nCheers, Heather',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 13:12:33'),(356,'5d049acd7a62cacab6a669c40af640af',109,6,'problem','I can\'t seem to add anymore pictures? I just bought a very cool 1977 Star Wars board game, in mint condition and I am trying to post a pic of it and it won\'t show?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 15:16:54'),(357,'65effa68d29e4d7bceb240f5356663ea',1,170,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 16:02:36'),(358,'5b088050116f020afa8f1b0917a404d7',59,5,'Picky & Naggin\'','Nope, it\'s not a band -- it\'s me with some CQ community notes ;)<br />\nA) I got a message her in the CQ community and I noticed a boo-boo of the oversight variety.  At the top of the message, where it says the name of who the message is from, why isn\'t that a link to the member\'s profile?  I sent a note to a member asking a question.  She replied, but there wasn\'t a super easy way to find her profile.  Sure, I may add her as a buddy, but right now I had to search for her and even if she was a buddy, why should I have to hunt for her?  It seems to me that I should just be able to click her name at the to of the message and get her profile, right?<br />\nB) The my buddies page (http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/buddies.html) should have something in the right column there... Maybe a way to see which of my buddies are online?  (Or maybe all profiles should have an icon for \'online now\'?)  Anyway, there\'s wasted space on that page and I don\'t believe in wasting space ;)<br />\nHope all is well.  I\'ll send a copy of this to Liz too.<br />\nD',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:04:18'),(359,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: Records','Hi Heather,<br />\nI\'m one of the writers for Collectors\' Quest, Deanna Dahlsad.  (So is my husband, Derek.)  We also have our own online stores and a silly pop culture/collecting blog (which is why Collectors\' Quest liked us, I guess lol)<br />\nSince Hubby and I play our records and keep darn near everything, we sell very few records. ;)<br />\nBe sure to put your real store name etc in your profile so that others can find you.  As this community grows, the selling/trading will take off more too.  (As trendy as it sounds, we\'re still in Beta I guess, with lots more to come.)<br />\nAnd I guess, while I am babbling, I\'m always interested in interviewing for articles here at CQ... Interested?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:11:50'),(360,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'M & M\'s and You','Howdy!<br />\nI write for Collectors\' Quest (http://www.collectorsquest.com/blog/index.php?author=3), and I\'d love, love, LOVE to interview you!  Are you interested?<br />\nPopTart aka Deanna Dahlsad',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:28:30'),(361,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',143,59,'RE: RE: RE: Records','Deanna,<br />\nI would be happy to be in an interview, that would be very groovy!<br />\nThis is such a great site and I will spread the word about it as I would love to see<br />\nit be the next big thing. I do not think there is one person out there that does not collect something, that would have to be a very dull and boring existance, ha ha<br />\nThe name of the online store is Flat Black and Beautiful Records and it is through Ebay, My bick and mortar store is \"Replay Entertainment Exchange\" and buy, sell and trade cd\'s,dvd\'s,video games, and of coarse my vinyl.<br />\nPlease feel free to contact me anytime.<br />\nThanks,<br />\nHeather Frarey',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:39:40'),(362,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',154,59,'RE: M & M\'s and You','Good evening Deanna<br />\nyea sounds great would Love to be a part of that<br />\nhow does it work ??<br />\nthrough email on phone or what?<br />\nas a matter of fact I had an artist here at my home today she wants to do drawings/paintings of a collector with their collection,<br />\nshe came over today took some pics did some scetches and then left<br />\nkaren',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:49:07'),(363,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'RE: RE: M & M\'s and You','Hi Karen,<br />\nEmail or this here messaging is fine for me, if that works for you...<br />\nI\'ve taken the liberty of including some starter questions -- if you\'d prefer to do this via the phone, just let me know :)<br />\nWhen did you begin collecting M&amp;M items?  Why?<br />\nHow many items in your collection?<br />\nWhat\'s the most extreme you\'ve gone for any item?  (distance travelled, most paid etc.)<br />\nDo you collect anything else?<br />\nWhat\'s a \'holy grail\' item you still seek?<br />\nTell me more about this artist &amp; the work...  What\'s the story behind it.  How did they find you?  What\'s the purpose of the art to be?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-24 02:25:28'),(364,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: RE: RE: Records','Hello Heather,<br />\nHere are some starter questions -- I\'ve taken the liberty to start here, but if you\'d prefer to do this via the phone, just let me know :)<br />\nWhen did you begin collecting records?  Why?<br />\nHow many items in your collection?<br />\nWhat\'s the most extreme you\'ve gone for any item?  (distance travelled, most paid etc.)<br />\nDo you collect anything else?<br />\nW