ood girl, really!)<br />\nI\'m continually amazed at the old smut, in terms of all the \'ism\'s that it portrays.  OK, and cuz I like smut too.  :p  But honestly, one learns much about \'humans\' and \'culture\' from these things.  It\'s like the conversations which went on in homes, at cocktail parties and in other settings -- things not for public consumption, but are indeed the \'who\' of what we are.  But I can (and often do) pontificate at my blog and so should spare you the lectures in such friendly conversation.  ;)<br />\nI have myself enjoyed your items -- and esp your ability to classify:  Star Wars &amp; Not Star Wars.  At first it made me giggle; but really, there is genius in such simplification.  I wish I had it.  (As this reply shows, I have not mastered simplification.  It will be my downfall.)<br />\nI\'ve made you a buddy -- and here at CQ, I don\'t even need your permission to do so.  Wish life were like that. :P<br />\nPlease, stay in touch -- and if not, let it be because you are busy with adding to your collections!<br />\nSPS',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-11-14 19:39:36'),(431,'1e4812084957adf4b24e1d13b5d2d1d6',109,68,'RE: RE: hey there','Hello Sps,<br />\nThanks for the add, I too will add you to my buddy\'s.  I worked as a historic researcher a few years back at our museum and I read all the news papers that was produced in my city.  It started in 1900 and I read as far as 1999 and it\'s amazing the things they wrote about, never today would news be produced in that manner.<br />\nI collect more than Star Wars, so I found it fitting to classify a heading that stated Non Star Wars :o)<br />\nAny way, thank you for the rely and please keep in touch with me aswell.  I love CQ, I am happy that I was asked to join.  Keep collecting and I look forward to seeing more or your collections as you upload them.<br />\nCarson Smith',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-11-16 07:04:44'),(432,'de175ea4b097ac1068db7281dcb4c9c7',1,197,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collector