8,'9d55b2238d9b7771ebf80e4edf878481',200,52,'RE: RE: Your Dino Collection','Hi dinocollector(Brian),<br />\nThanks for responding to my message. I collect mostly comics and cards and I agree the hunt is the fun in collecting.<br />\nI had more that I wanted to share when I wrote and didn\'t have all the info at the time. Did you see the comic books(GN) called \"Dinosaurs A Celebration\"?<br />\nThis was a four part series (I only have 1 &amp; 2, I don\'t know if they were all published) by Marvel/Epic in late 1992. Number 1 was \"Terrible Claws and Tyrants\" and number 2 was  \"Egg Stealers and Earth Shakers\". These are great books with much info about many different dinosaurs and nice art too. These are the kind of thing you share with young or old that are interested in learning more about dinosaurs. You probably already know all this info, but you might not know about these books.<br />\nDo you have any Wacko-Saurs stickers in your collection? This series is by Zoot and was produced in 1987. This is a fun series, not a serious set.<br />\nThere was a three part series of comics based on the \"Dinosaurs Attack!\" card set published in 1991 by Eclipse. I only have the first issue and it has a dinosaur (that looks like a water type) wrapped around and breaking the Statue of Liberty and being attacked by helicopters. I sometimes get a book because of the cover art. If you want more info about the card set, how and who were involved in this series I can come up with some web pages that explain.<br />\nI was able to identify the wrapper missing from your picture. If you would like to have all three wrappers in your collection, let me know and I will send my address and then you send me a S.A.S.E. and I will send the missing wrapper as an unopened pack, gratis.<br />\nI like to read and a story I remember from my childhood was called(I think) \"The Shy Stegosaurus of Crippled Creek\" and was about some kids and an invisible Stegosaur. Does this sound familiar?<br />\nI\'ve read stories at Yahoo about some dinosaur finds lately, have you seen these stories? Then I saw something about what might be a new species. I\'ll send the article if you are interested.<br />\nThanks for sharing your enthusiasm for collecting.<br />\nJohn(jac)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-12-06 03:15:59'),(449,'02279e6dd7eba212af82ceff95741a1c',1,210,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2007-12-06 18:25:37'),(450,'8620539c3be2d313796f2a5a7bf65181',171,69,'collections','bonjour, je rÃ©alise des videos sur le monde des collections, que je diffuse sur un blog, l\'ami des collectionneurs\"  cela devrais vous intÃ©resser, et si vous Ãªtes d\'accord, j\'aimerai faire un portrait de vos collections surt ce blog. Cordialement<br />\nrÃ©my<br />\nhttp://web.mac.com/remy.deveze',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-12-07 05:02:23'),(451,'88489e3720f33afb3e269be3f2575009',171,89,'collections','bonjour, je rÃ©alise des videos sur le monde des collections, que je diffuse sur un blog, l\'ami des collectionneurs\"  cela devrais vous intÃ©resser, et si vous Ãªtes d\'accord, j\'aimerai faire un portrait de vos collections surt ce blog. Cordialement<br />\nrÃ©my<br />\nhttp://web.mac.com/remy.deveze',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2007-12-07 05:03:29'),(452,'32d9d5816a0135cb60a2ea28941469f4',171,130,'portrait','bonjour, je rÃ©alise des videos sur le monde des collections, que je diffuse sur un blog, l\'ami des collectionneurs\"  cela devrais vous intÃ©resser, et si vous Ãªtes d\'accord, j\'aimerai faire un portrait de vos collections surt ce blog. Cordialement<br />\nrÃ©my<br />\nhttp://web.mac.com/rem