href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,1,0,0,0,0,'2008-03-31 20:47:18'),(580,'33067b0f56a65cf37c420e4880b433ef',90,503,'RE: Uni Help','It\'s a waste, you won\'t believe how much they might be worth now :)<br />\nSo, for your questions:<br />\n1. I\'ve started collecting on my honeymoon last July. we bought our first pez around July 6th I think.<br />\n2. I\'ve been looking for something to collect for a long time. collecting adds something to your life. On July 1st, just before we flew to Paris for our honeymoon, we saw a video article about an Israeli pez collector, showing her entire collection. This brought some childhood memories, and made me realize that it\'s what I\'ve been waiting for!<br />\n3. My most valuable piece will be the incredible hulk - no feet.<br />\nThis has both the money value and the sentimental value.<br />\nWe received this vintage dispenser as a gift from a Pez friend we made online, and it\'s also worth around $50 on the market.<br />\n4. I used to catalog them using a software a Pezhead wrote, however, since I installed windows Vista on my machine, it doesn\'t work anymore.<br />\n5. My collection used to be stored, until we bought our new apartment.<br />\nNow it lays in glass display cabinets at the center of our apartment, right between the living room and the kitchen. we currently have 5 display cabinets and we\'re starting to run out of space in them :)<br />\n6. Collecting adds something to your life, it adds another meaning besides the day to day work, and the routine at home.<br />\nAnother thing is that Pez has all those lovely characters on the dispensers that spark memories, or just bring up a smile.<br />\nThere is the excitement from the hunt of a new dispenser, starting from finding the person who has it, finding a trade or the right price, picking it up from the post office, the unpacking of the box, and to see it displayed next to all your items.<br />\n7. We\'re about to have a baby very soon, so it might slow the collection a bit.<br />\nHowever, I do not intend to stop collecting any time soon. I can see me collecting Pez 10 years from now.<br />\nPez Co. makes sure you will keep collecting by adding more and more dispensers each year, while making them better and better each time.<br />\nIf you have any questions, please let me know.<br />\nGood luck with your project!<br />\nBTW: I donno anyone from Australia, so u\'r the first :)<br />\nIf you have MSN messenger, i\'m always there - fasteril@gmail.com<br />\n-Ran',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2008-04-01 00:45:04'),(581,'33067b0f56a65cf37c420e4880b433ef',503,90,'RE: Uni Help','Oh wow!<br />\nThanks for your help! You have by far the most interesting survey I\'ve done so far :)<br />\nI forgot to ask you how many you have in your collection now? Do you even keep count?<br />\nBy the looks of your photos its hundreds! I can\'t believe you only start collecting less than a year ago. I think you\'ve inspired me to start collecting something! Maybe I will start on my honeymoon too! hehe I\'ll have to wait a few years before that though!<br />\nPS I am trying to add you on msn. It is stuffing up though - I\'ll keep trying but if not my email is flairee@hotmail.com<br />\nThanks again :)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2008-04-01 04:13:42'),(582,'33067b0f56a65cf37c420e4880b433ef',90,503,'RE: Uni Help','Hi again,<br />\nI have about 600 different pez items, and there are more packages on the way :)<br />\nI wish I started earlier, if I only saw that article earlier :)<br />\nIf you start a collection, make sure it something that means something to you.<br />\nI didn\'t relate to all the coke cans, lighters, knives, hats, kinder... the Pez reached out to me :)<br />\nI added you to MSN with the email you sent me.',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2008-04-01 04:18:21'),(583,'e412cd692bdfc8352cae5e3be3a61b6e',1,522,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collecto