and have yet to look at the rest, but if they are as awesome as what Ive seen so far....<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWOW.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nId love to see a large group shot of all your stuff if you\'ve got one. You really are a serious collector arent you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI do admire your will tho in being able to open all the cards. Its the one thing I cant seem to bring myself to do yet. I got a few figures opened but those cases I have two. Most my opened stuff is from when I was a kid and some how managed to hang on to it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIm looking forward to checking out the rest of your DC galleries as those intrige me the most.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAwesome stuff to say the least. Keep collecting and enjoy your collections as only a true collector can. You given me something to shoot for now.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHave a nice day.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDougM',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2009-08-15 09:19:42'),(1771,'4721b05ad2c1f1d6464c095d4920c52d',12,502,'your collections','Thanks for the kind words! My biggest problem is that I have NO display space, and also no space to keep everything in the packages, which is why I go through everything once a year and tear it all open.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI tend to see it all as potential art, and all of it as active inspiration. This kind of stuff inspired me to start sculpting my own toys. You can see some stuff here : http://resonantfish.com/<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd other stuff here : http://resonantfish.bigcartel.com/<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe scariest part is that these things don\'t even scrape the surface of what I\'ve collected over the last 15 years. There are at least 20 waves of Heroclix that I haven\'t had the time to photo yet, and stacks of.... everything. I\'m sometimes surprised that I\'ve amassed to much, especially since I make barely over minimum wage, but I pick up a lot of illustration and writing jobs on the side too. I guess that\'s the cost of collecting sometimes - absolutely no free time. It\'s a really crazy balance to maintain, and lately, I\'ve severely cut back just so I could have time to breathe.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHow do you balance life and collecting?<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAwesome to hear from a fellow collector!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCollin',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2009-08-15 09:59:04'),(1772,'4721b05ad2c1f1d6464c095d4920c52d',502,12,'your collections','Hey man.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you have more stuff unpictured, then you really are a serious collector. Same here. I got a bunch of figures I havent pictured yet, takes so long to take the pic, edit it for size, then upload to site, info pic and post.<br />\r\nWork takes lots of my time too. But I still get days where I find time to go through and get a few pics. I try to always pic new items as I get them. That way there is one less to do later, LOL.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI leave everything packaged because in some cases I love the artwork on the cards and boxes. Some stuff is as cool or cooler than the comics so thats one reason everything stays MIB. Also I cant bring myself to open much of it. The puzzles are gonna be framed and put on the wall in my new dispplay room tho.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI have a wife that is very understanding in regards to my hobby. Heck she has her parents looking around yard sales and flea markets for anything that might be cool to add to my collections. Last week for example they found me a couple of new Superman Returns loose figures that I didnt have. Now I do and they are on the shelf with the few loose figures I actually opened the one ofs I got.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUsually for B-Days and X-Mas I have friends and family that get me more stuff too. ts kinda a family thing around here.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are currently in the process of building a house. We got the basement and ground floor done and next week the guys should have the second floor and roof done. When the interior is done I have a nice large display room designed to house alll my stuff in. When I put stuff in there then I plan to take pics of everything and get a nice catalogue going of what I actually have. I have boxes of stuff backed away and drawers filled with all kinds of stuff unseen in ages. So my new display room will house plenty of more stuff that very few have seen since I picked it up years ago. When the new pics are taken I will be posting them around here and hope you enjoy them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHave a nice day and I hope your summer is going well. Take care and keep collecting what you do. You have an amazing collection and Im in awe of the figures you\'ve gotten.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDougM',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2009-08-15 10:19:13'),(1773,'a543df41a4b20af4db4888da5f29866d',1327,1441,'Lion King for sale','Okay, great thanks for keeping my link in your favourites! <br />\r\n<br />\r\nBest wishes in your job hunting. And your English is good - I could understand everything! =) <br />\r\n<br />\r\nSureHope',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2009-08-15 21:46:04'),(1774,'a42e82568e018958ba1d783855917f00',1,1451,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\n\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\n\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,1,0,0,0,0,'2009-08-16 08:21:20'),(1775,'2a39507a454e7f48b3977fd518b17a85',1,1452,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\n\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\n\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,1,0,0,0,0,'2009-08-16 13:00:17'),