ors.\n\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\n\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2009-11-15 15:33:31'),(2095,'9205a0f4c42f1c4839325d171b1554eb',1,1651,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\n\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\n\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2009-11-15 15:49:33'),(2096,'2a5d559b4ee0af8c278a37b0283e0ca9',1400,1637,'Harry Potter','1) My collection is everything to me. I have been collecting for over 8 years, and Harry Potter has been one of the only constants in my life. I couldn\'t say what the value my collection is to society, I\'ve never had it displayed in public or anything, but my friends love it!!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) Since I mostly buy my HP collectibles second hand, I don\'t usually have to pay much for items; but I do buy many things new. The most expensive item I\'ve bought would have to be a Lionel train set of the Hogwarts Express, that was about $200.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3) I\'ve never actually counted the number of items in my collection, but I\'d guess anywhere between 600-800 pieces.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n4) No, I have never had an opportunity to go to an auction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n5) The only thing I can think of is when I walked around stalking some women who was carrying the last Harry Potter figure in the store to see If she was going to buy it. And she did end up buying it, so I found the nearest store that had one left, and drove about and hour away to buy the last one they had.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n6) I have not yet gone to a Harry Potter convention, but I really want to and plan on going to at least one in the near future.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n7) I mostly find/buy my HP stuff at thrift stores, second hand stores, swapmeets and garage sales. So when I\'m looking, I try to keep a look out for certain colors &amp; patterns common on the packaging of HP items. I also like to look thoroughly throughout the store, because there are so many different Harry Potter collectibles other than the common games and toys; you never know what you\'re going to find!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n8) Because of HP, I have made some of the best of friends and met some of the nicest people. Harry Potter has kept me connected with my childhood and opened up my eyes to so many things, and I am forever grateful for that.',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2009-11-15 20:37:15'),(2097,'fe567dde89d0afb9611b9caf951bd0e5',1637,1401,'Sorry I forgot to say why','Thanks for your help.',0,0,1,0,0,0,'2009-11-15 22:45:33'),(2098,'61ef439140fde95ee72945b028cf44f9',1,1652,'Welcome to Collectors\' Quest','Welcome to Collectors\' Quest - the destination place for all collectors.\n\nGet started by <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection/create.html\">adding your own collection</a> or just click around to find some great <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/collection.html\">collections</a> and <a href=\"http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/collectors.html\">collectors</a>.\n\nWhat\'s in your collection?',1,0,0,0,0,0,'2009-11-16 14:41:16'),(2099,'2a5d559b4ee0af8c278a37b0283e0ca9',1637,1400,'Harry Potter','Thank you so much, your answers were very helpful.',0,0,1,0,0,0,'2009-11-17 09:22:07'),(2100,'56be15852895580eee2f473dd13488ed',1610,1281,'Oscar cookie jar','Hello Susan:<br />\r\nI was anxious to hear back from you regarding Oscar.  I hope you didn\'t take offense to my delay in getting back to you.  I ca